<h1>{$node_name}</h1>

<p>The option “Domains” of the Menu “Email” in Elastix lets us view and configure the domains in the email server.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/email_domains.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 1</div>
<br />

<h3>View and Delete</h3>

<p>Clicking on the names of the domains will bring us to a screen that shows the data of the domain.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/email_domains_view_del.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 2</div>
<br />

<p>To delete a domain, click on the “Delete” button.</p>

<h3>Create Domain</h3>

<p>To add a domain, click on the “Create Domain” button. A form will be shown where you will input the name of the new domain.</p>

<div><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/email_domains_create.jpg" border="0"></div>
<div>Figure 3</div>
<br />

